age of chinese civilization. ethnic chinese consider themselves to be part of the 'han' race till this day. the collapse of the han dynasty in 220 ce led to a period of political turmoil and war known as the three kingdoms period, which saw china split into the three separate states of wei, shu and wu. despite lasting for only about 60 years, it is a highly romanticised period of chinese history. china was then briefly reunified under the jin dynasty, before descending into a period of division and anarchy once again. the era of division culminated with the sui 